{"overview":"This 69-bar piece in C# minor exhibits a clear through-composed arc with recapitulatory elements, moving through a network of diatonic modulations—touching E major, B minor, F# major, and G# minor—before resolving firmly home; its most distinctive feature is the sustained nocturne-like texture of sustained bass octaves beneath continuous triplet arpeggios, which persists across nearly all formal sections and lends the piece its meditative, song-without-words character. The extended developmental section (bars 23–42) with its prolonged dominant pedal on G# and climactic arpeggiated figuration provides the emotional apex, while the coda's oscillating i–V gestures and deceptive cadence at bar 67 give the close an air of resigned, inward finality.","cross_piece_tags":["nocturne","ternary","lyrical","meditative","melancholic","arpeggiated_bass","pedal_point","circle_of_fifths"]}
